cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the detection of AI-generated fake face images or videos, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also discusses the errors introduced during the splicing of synthesized face regions, which can be considered as a security and privacy issue (cs.CR). The proposed method involves the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically support vector machines (SVM), which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories.
